===Etymology===
From {{inh|fr|frm|resver}}, from {{inh|fr|fro|resver||to consider, reflect, be delirious}}, of {{unk|fr|nocap=1|title=uncertain}} origin. The ''Trésor de la langue française informatisé'' links it back either to an unattested {{m|fro|*esver||to wander}} or to Latin {{m|la|*reexvadō}}, from {{af|la|re-|ex-|evadō|nocat=1}}<ref>{{R:TLFi|etym=1}}</ref>. The ''Französisches Etymologisches Wörterbuch'' links it back to {{m|la|*reexvagus}}, hence the same as the first proposal by the ''Trésor de la langue française informatisé''<ref>{{R:FEW|100|184|title=*reexvagus}}</ref>. Compare {{noncog|ang|rǣswan|t=to consider, suspect, conjecture}}, of similar form and meaning.

